: 400;\">Center for the Integration of Research, Teaching, and Learning</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (CIRTL)’s mission is to enhance excellence in undergraduate education through the development of a national faculty committed to implementing and advancing effective teaching practices for diverse learners as part of successful and varied professional careers. It was established with the intent of preparing future science, technology, engineering, and mathematics (STEM) faculty across the nation, to ultimately improve the STEM learning of all students, at every college and university, and thereby to increase the diversity in STEM fields and the STEM literacy of the nation. The three CIRTL core ideas are: Evidence-based Teaching, Learning Communities, and Learning-through-Diversity.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">ISU’s membership in CIRTL is sponsored in a partnership between CELT and the Graduate College. This 2011 </span><a href=\"http://archive.inside.iastate.edu/2011/1103/cirtl.php\"><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Inside Iowa State</span></i><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> article describes how ISU became involved in CIRTL</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The links below provide more information.</span>','CIRTL','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. In quis aliquet nulla. Aliquam erat volutpat. Morbi nibh lorem, pellentesque vitae nibh nec.','inherit','closed','closed','','34-revision-v1','','','2015-09-01 17:52:48','2015-09-01 17:52:48','',34,'www.celt-staging.com2015/09/01/34-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(115,1,'2015-09-01 17:53:37','2015-09-01 17:53:37','<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">CELT’s Graduate Student Teaching Certificate (GSTC) aims to enhance the professional </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">development of graduate students who want to become professors in four-year schools of higher education emphasizing teaching. 