ss=\"p4\"><strong>Funding:</strong> Up to $1,000 per proposal</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>How to Apply:</strong> Complete the online <span class=\"s6\">application form </span>or down load and submit this <span class=\"s6\">paper form.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"p4\">Program Details</h3>\r\n<p class=\"p4\">This program is designed to support the development of Graduate Learning Communities (GLC) to help graduate students (Masters and PhD) with first-year transitions to graduate school. Departments, graduate programs, and graduate student organizations are invited to propose GLCs that:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"ul1\">\r\n  <li class=\"li4\">Help incoming graduate students successfully make the transition from undergraduate to graduate school by building community</li>\r\n <li class=\"li4\">Provide time and opportunities for students to strategize how to thrive in graduate school</li>\r\n <li class=\"li4\">Integrate the different components of the 1st year graduate experience, e.g. course-work, research, etc.</li>\r\n <li class=\"li4\">Engage graduate students early in the scholarly life of the department or program</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<h2 class=\"p12\"></h2>\r\n<h2 class=\"p12\"><span class=\"s5\">Grant Program: </span>Course Development Grants</h2>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Sponsored by:</strong> Engineering-LAS Online (ELO), CELT, Graduate College, and CIRTL</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Eligible applicants:</strong> ISU Graduate Students, Postdocs, Faculty, and Staff</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Due date:</strong>  March 30, 2015 for courses to be offered Fall 2015, and September 15, 2015 for courses to be offered Spring 2016.</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>Funding:</strong> Up to $3,000 per course credit hour</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\"><strong>How to Apply:</strong> Complete the online <span class=\"s6\">application form</span> or down load and submit this <span class=\"s6\">paper form version </span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"p7\">Program Details<