rces are also in place to support instructors who are negotiating challenging student-teacher interactions. Many of these key resources are offered through the Dean of Students Office (insert link &lt; http://www.dso.iastate.edu/&gt; ).\r\n<h2>Faculty and Staff Guide of Student Assistance</h2>\r\nThe Dean of Students Office has created a <a href=\"http://www.studentassistance.dso.iastate.edu/faculty-and-staff-guide\">detailed guide</a> on what to do, and where to find assistance in addressing a variety of situations than may arise with students. This is a good place to start to help you determine next steps.\r\n<h2>Promoting Student Academic Success</h2>\r\n<i>Academic Success Center provides a collection of services and programs designed to help students reach their academic goals. The staff offer individualized and group experiences through course-specific and general academic assistance as well as credit and non-credit programs. The Center facilitates </i>PSYCH 131, <i>a 1-credit academic learning skills seminar for undergraduate students. The Center also provides a number of online resources (insert link http://www.asc.dso.iastate.edu/resources) on targeted topics such as study skills, time management, goal setting and test anxiety. </i>\r\n\r\n(Supporting and Promoting Self-Directed Learners - Academic Success Center\r\n\r\n<span class=\"s1\">Insert video in right hand column? </span>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FqZJdef2rzM<span class=\"s1\">)</span>\r\n\r\n<span class=\"s2\">Writing and Media Center</span> helps students become stronger, more confident writers and communicators. The WMC offers tailored, one-on-one conferences for students from all disciplines who are working on any form of written, oral, visual, or electronic communication.\r\n\r\n<span class=\"s2\">Student Disability Resources</span> office works collaboratively with ISU teaching professionals to promote opportunities of educational success of each student with a disability.\r\n\r\n(Your Role in the Life of a Student with a Disability\r\n\r\nInsert video in right hand column? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7UsofBEI8FQ\r\n\r\nClass Attendance Policy (insert link: http://catalog.iastate.edu/academiclife/regulations/#classattendancetext) is outlined in the ISU Course Catalog and reads in part:\r\n\r\n“Students are expected to attend class meetings as scheduled. Each instructor sets his or her policy with respect to class attendance, and excuses for absence from class are handled between the student and instructor. The instructor is expected to announce his or her policy at the beginning of the course.”\r\n<h2>Promoting Diversity and Inclusion</h2>\r\nA number of offices on campus support creating a diverse and inclusive campus environment, and can help faculty foster this type of learning environment in their classroom.\r\n\r\nOffice of Diversity, Equity, and Community (insert link: http://www.diversity.iastate.edu/) (Office of Senior Vice President and Provost)\r\n\r\nInternational Students and Scholars<span class=\"s1\"> (Division of Student Affairs)</span>\r\n\r\nLesbian Gay Bisexual Transgender Student Services <i>(Dean of Students Office)</i>\r\n\r\nMulticultural Student Affairs <i>(Dean of Students Office)</i>\r\n\r\nReligious Accommodations  <i>(Office of Equal Opportunity)</i>\r\n\r\n<i>Veterans Center</i>\r\n\r\n<i>Women’s Center, Sloss House (Dean of Students Office)</i>\r\n\r\nAcademic Integrity: The Faculty Role\r\n\r\n(Insert video in right hand column? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pQGhlXiFazU\r\n\r\nPromoting Academic Integrity\r\n\r\nThe Office of Student Conduct( insert link: <span class=\"s2\">http://www.studentconduct.dso.iastate.edu/fac-staff</span>) (formerly known as the Office of Judicial Affairs) provides support for faculty, staff, and students when dealing with a range of student conduct issues including academic integrity.\r\n\r\nThe Pathway to Inclusive Classrooms and Working with Diverse Students\r\n\r\n(Insert video in right hand column? https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=pZCKYjHLFbo\r\n\r\nEnsuring Student Safety\r\n\r\nThe ISU Environmental Health and Safety (insert link: http://www.ehs.iastate.edu/prep/students) unit and ISU Police provide resources to help faculty in case of emergencies related to student behaviors either in or out of a classroom. The ISU Course Catalog also includes information specific to addressing disruptive classroom behavior\r\n\r\n<span class=\"s1\"> (insert link : </span>http://catalog.iastate.edu/academiclife/regulations/#classroomdisruptiontext<span class=\"s1\">) </span>\r\n\r\nViolent Incident Response Training (VIRT)<span class=\"s1\"> (ISU Police)</span>\r\n\r\nRecognizing and Reporting Disturbing Behavior (RRDB)<span class=\"s1\"> (ISU Police)</span>','Campus Resources to Support Students','','publish','closed','closed','','campus-resources-to-support-students','','','2015-09-27 18:55:44','2015-09-27 18:55:44','',192,'www.celt-staging.com?page_id=206',0,'page','',0),(207,1,'2015-09-27 18:55:44','2015-09-27 18:55:44','Iowa State University has a comprehensive network of resources designed to support students throughout their undergraduate experience. Some of these resources are also in place to support instructors who are negotiating challenging student-teacher interactions. Many of these key resources are offered through the Dean of Students Office (insert link &lt; http://www.dso.iastate.edu/&gt; ).\r\n<h2>Faculty and Staff Guide of Student Assistance</h2>\r\nThe Dean of Students Office has created a <a href=\"http://www.studentassistance.dso.iastate.edu/faculty-and-staff-guide\">detailed guide</a> on what to do, and where to find assistance in addressing a variety of situations than may arise with students. This is a good place to start to help you determine next steps.\r\n<h2>Promoting Student Academic Success</h2>\r\n<i>Academic Success Center provides a collection of services and programs designed to help students reach their academic goals. Th