king with CELT and the SVPP, Karen worked for two years as an Administrative Specialist with the School of Education.\r\n\r\nKaren holds a B.A. in Psychology from McGill University. She is currently pursuing her M.Ed. in Higher Education with a concentration in Leadership and Learning.','Karen Couves','','inherit','closed','closed','','485-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 04:32:34','2015-11-16 04:32:34','',485,'www.celt-staging.com2015/11/16/485-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(488,1,'2015-11-16 04:34:03','2015-11-16 04:34:03','Lesya leads technical and pedagogical support of audience response technology, also known as clickers. Her primary duties revolve around the design, development and implementation of faculty training opportunities for meaningful and effective applications of instructional technologies, including clickers. Lesya is responsible for producing clicker on-line support materials and informing/involving the vendor in troubleshooting and problem-solving surrounding clickers.\r\n\r\nLesya is interested in the concept of sustainable online course design and development and collaborates on faculty-led projects that advance teaching and learning via instructional technologies. Lesya earned her doctoral degree in Curriculum and Instructional Technology from Iowa State University’s College of Education in 2007.','Lesya Hassall','','publish','closed','closed','','lesya-hassall','','','2015-11-16 13:53:56','2015-11-16 13:53:56','',465,'www.celt-staging.com?page_id=488',0,'page','',0),(489,1,'2015-11-16 04:33:48','2015-11-16 04:33:48','','Lesya Hassall','Lesya Hassall Profile','inherit','closed','closed','','lesyahassall','','','2015-11-16 04:33:54','2015-11-16 04:33:54','',488,'www.celt-staging.comwp-content/uploads/2015/11/LesyaHassall.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(490,1,'2015-11-16 04:34:03','2015-11-16 04:34:03','Lesya leads technical and pedagogical support of audience response technology, also known as clickers. Her primary duties revolve around t