ough CELT include the Miller Faculty Fellowship, SoTL Institute, and Teaching Partners Program. Marcketti is an Associate Professor in the Apparel, Events, and Hospitality Management Department. Her teaching and research interests include the scholarship of teaching and learning, apparel industry history, and creative thinking enhancement and development.\r\n\r\nMarcketti earned an A.B. in art history and a M.S. in textiles, merchandising, and interiors from the University of Georgia and a doctoral degree in apparel, merchandising, and design with a minor in higher education from Iowa State University. Her teaching and research efforts have been recognized through college, university, and national awards such as the Early Achievement in Teaching Award, Iowa State University; Pacesetter Award, The University of Georgia, and Rising Star Award, International Textile and Apparel Association. Sara currently serves as the Vice President of Publications for the Costume Society of America and Vice President of Professional Development for the Iowa Association of Family and Consumer Sciences.','Sara Marcketti','','inherit','closed','closed','','500-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 13:57:22','2015-11-16 13:57:22','',500,'www.celt-staging.com2015/11/16/500-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(525,1,'2015-11-16 13:58:02','2015-11-16 13:58:02','Wei joined CELT in December 2012. Her primary duty is to help faculty members develop instructional strategy for technology integration and provide consultation support for pedagogical resources. The responsibilities of this position also includes university-wide user support for the course management software Blackboard including, but not limited to, managing course and user accounts, providing instructor phone, email and face-to-face support. This position is responsible for participating in collaborative user support activities with other university IT and academic departments. A part of the job duties includes developing teaching seminars or workshops to help faculty engage students learning.\r\n\r\nWei holds a M.S. in Education and she is currently pursuing a Ph.D. in Education with emphasis in Curriculum and Instructional Technology and Human-Computer Interaction. CELT provides her various opportunities to further develop practical and theoretical knowledge in instructional design that she loves. Her research interests include designing and developing training instructional materials and investigating teachers’ technology integration skills through the Technological Pedagogical Content Knowledge framework.','Wei Wang','','inherit','closed','closed','','506-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 13:58:02','2015-11-16 13:58:02','',506,'www.celt-staging.com2015/11/16/506-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(526,1,'2015-11-16 13:58:48','2015-11-16 13:58:48','Zina Alaswad is a PhD student at the School of Education. She completed her Master’s degree in Fine Arts and is interested in education and instructional technologies as tools for enhancing the learning experience for students. ZIna provides faculty support for technologies for teaching and learning.','Zina Alaswad','','inherit','closed','closed','','509-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 13:58:48','2015-11-16 13:58:48','',509,'www.celt-staging.com2015/11/16/509-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(527,1,'2015-11-16 16:57:09','2015-11-16 16:57:09','Ann Marie VanDerZanden is Director of the Center for Excellence in Learning and Teaching and professor of Horticulture at Iowa State University.\r\n\r\nIn her role as director, VanDerZanden provides leadership for the center in meeting its mission to support, promote, and enhance teaching effectiveness and student learning at Iowa State. She provides individual faculty consultations and facilitates faculty and graduate student workshops on learning outcomes, effective teaching practice, preparing for the first week of class, and how to create a good syllabus.\r\n\r\nShe also maintains an active teaching and mentoring role in the Department of Horticulture. Prior to her appointment to CELT in 2009, VanDerZanden had a significant teaching and advising role in the department. She currently teaches the capstone landscape design course, advises undergraduates in the Planting Design, Installation and Management option in the department and is the advisor for the ISU Landscape Club. She has been recognized for her excellent teaching through numerous awards including the 2010 American Society for Horticulture Science Outstanding Undergraduate Educator and the 2012 ISU Louis Thompson Distinguished Undergraduate Teaching Award. In 2013 she was selected as a Fellow of the American Society for Horticulture Science.\r\n\r\nVanDerZanden has been a faculty member at ISU since 2003. She is a member of the North American Colleges and Teachers of Agriculture and served six years as chair of the Educational Issues and Teaching Improvement Committee. She is currently serving as the Midwest Region Director for this organization. She is also an active member of the International Society for the Scholarship of Teaching and Learning (ISSoTL) and the Professional and Organizational Development Network in Higher Education (POD).','Ann Marie VanDerZanden','','inherit','closed','closed','','469-revision-v1','','','2015-11-16 16:57:09','2015-11-16 16:57:09','',469,'www.celt-staging.com2015/11/16/469-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(528,1,'2015-11-16 17:02:30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2015-11-16 17:02:30','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'www.celt-staging.com?page_id=528',0,'page','',0),(529,1,'2015-11-16 19:36:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2015-11-16 19:36:16','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'www.celt-staging.com?page_id=529',0,'page','',0),(530,1,'2015-11-23 02:42:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','open','','','','','2015-11-23 02:42:32','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http: